# Hearst Design System Token Usage Guidelines

## CRITICAL: Always Use Design Tokens

When creating or modifying any component, storybook page, or style, you MUST use the design tokens from `@/lib/designTokens`. Never hardcode colors, spacing, typography, or other design values.

## Token Import Pattern

Always import tokens at the top of your file:

```typescript
import { 
  colors, 
  spacing, 
  typography, 
  font, 
  border, 
  layout, 
  elevation,
  breakpoints,
  primitives 
} from '@/lib/designTokens';
```

## Token Categories and Usage

### Colors (`colors`)
- `colors.neutral` - Gray scale (100-1000, lightest, darkest)
- `colors.brand` - Brand colors (1-14)
- `colors.primary` - Primary color scale (100-1000)
- `colors.alert.success/warning/error/info` - Alert colors
- `colors.content` - Semantic content colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
backgroundColor: colors.neutral[100]
color: colors.neutral.darkest
borderColor: colors.neutral[300]

// ❌ WRONG - Never hardcode colors
backgroundColor: '#f5f5f5'
color: '#121212'
```

### Spacing (`spacing`)
- `spacing.none` = 0
- `spacing['3xs']` = 2
- `spacing['2xs']` = 4
- `spacing.xs` = 8
- `spacing.sm` = 12
- `spacing.md` = 16
- `spacing.lg` = 20
- `spacing.xl` = 24
- `spacing['2xl']` = 32
- `spacing['3xl']` = 48
- `spacing['4xl']` = 64

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
padding: spacing.lg
gap: spacing.md
margin: `${spacing.xl}px`

// ❌ WRONG
padding: 20
gap: 16
```

### Typography (`typography`, `font`)
Use typography presets for consistent text styles:
- `typography.display.lg/md/sm` - Large headlines
- `typography.heading.xl/lg/md/sm` - Section headings
- `typography.body.lg/md/sm` - Body text
- `typography.caption.md/sm` - Small text/labels
- `typography.button.lg/md/sm` - Button text

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
<h1 style={{ ...typography.display.md, color: colors.neutral.darkest }}>
<p style={{ ...typography.body.md, color: colors.neutral[600] }}>

// For individual properties:
fontSize: font.size.lg
fontWeight: font.weight.bold
fontFamily: font.family.default
```

### Border (`border`)
- `border.radius.none/sm/md/lg/xl/2xl/full`
- `border.width.none/thin/medium/thick`

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
borderRadius: border.radius.md
border: `${border.width.thin}px solid ${colors.neutral[300]}`
```

### Layout (`layout`)
Container and component widths:
- `layout['4xs']` = 128
- `layout['3xs']` = 192
- `layout['2xs']` = 224
- `layout.xs` = 256
- `layout.sm` = 320
- `layout.md` = 384
- `layout.lg` = 512
- `layout.xl` = 768
- `layout['2xl']` = 1024
- `layout['3xl']` = 1280
- `layout['4xl']` = 1600

### Breakpoints (`breakpoints`)
- `breakpoints.sm` = 320
- `breakpoints.md` = 768
- `breakpoints.lg` = 1024
- `breakpoints.xl` = 1440
- `breakpoints['2xl']` = 1600

### Elevation (`elevation`)
- `elevation.none/sm/md/lg/xl/2xl`

## Brand-Specific Theming

For brand-specific components, import from `@/lib/brandThemes`:

```typescript
import { brandThemes, getTheme } from '@/lib/brandThemes';

// Get a specific brand theme
const theme = getTheme('carAndDriver');

// Use theme colors
backgroundColor: theme.colors.primary
color: theme.colors.text
```

## Component Template

When creating a new component, follow this pattern:

```typescript
'use client';

import { colors, spacing, typography, border, font } from '@/lib/designTokens';

interface MyComponentProps {
  // props
}

export function MyComponent({ ...props }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div
      style={{
        padding: spacing.lg,
        backgroundColor: colors.neutral.lightest,
        borderRadius: border.radius.md,
        border: `1px solid ${colors.neutral[300]}`,
      }}
    >
      <h2 style={{ ...typography.heading.lg, color: colors.neutral.darkest }}>
        Title
      </h2>
      <p style={{ ...typography.body.md, color: colors.neutral[600] }}>
        Content
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Storybook Page Template

When creating a storybook documentation page:

```typescript
'use client';

import { colors, spacing, typography, border, font } from '@/lib/designTokens';
import { MyComponent } from '@/components/MyComponent';

export default function MyComponentPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ padding: spacing['3xl'], maxWidth: 1200, margin: '0 auto' }}>
      {/* Header */}
      <div style={{ marginBottom: spacing['3xl'] }}>
        <h1 style={{ ...typography.display.md, color: colors.neutral.darkest, margin: 0 }}>
          Component Name
        </h1>
        <p style={{ ...typography.body.lg, color: colors.neutral[600], margin: `${spacing.md}px 0 0` }}>
          Component description
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Preview */}
      <section style={{ marginBottom: spacing['3xl'] }}>
        <h2 style={{ ...typography.heading.lg, color: colors.neutral.darkest, marginBottom: spacing.lg }}>
          Preview
        </h2>
        <div
          style={{
            backgroundColor: colors.neutral[200],
            borderRadius: border.radius.lg,
            padding: spacing.xl,
            border: `1px solid ${colors.neutral[300]}`,
          }}
        >
          <MyComponent />
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Token Source

All tokens are sourced from the Hearst Design System API:
`https://figma-connector.kubeprod.hearstapps.com/token-studio/tokens`

The resolved values are stored in `src/lib/designTokens.ts`.
